{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:lamentations.5",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "lamentations",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Lamentations 5 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:1",
      "text": "Remember, O Lord, what has befallen us; behold, and see our disgrace!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:2",
      "text": "Our inheritance has been turned over to strangers, our homes to aliens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:3",
      "text": "We have become orphans, fatherless; our mothers are like widows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:4",
      "text": "We must pay for the water we drink, the wood we get must be bought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:5",
      "text": "With a yoke on our necks we are hard driven; we are weary, we are given no rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:6",
      "text": "We have given the hand to Egypt, and to Assyria, to get bread enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:7",
      "text": "Our fathers sinned, and are no more; and we bear their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:8",
      "text": "Slaves rule over us; there is none to deliver us from their hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:9",
      "text": "We get our bread at the peril of our lives, because of the sword in the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:10",
      "text": "Our skin is hot as an oven with the burning heat of famine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:11",
      "text": "Women are ravished in Zion, virgins in the towns of Judah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:12",
      "text": "Princes are hung up by their hands; no respect is shown to the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:13",
      "text": "Young men are compelled to grind at the mill; and boys stagger under loads of wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:14",
      "text": "The old men have quit the city gate, the young men their music.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:15",
      "text": "The joy of our hearts has ceased; our dancing has been turned to mourning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:16",
      "text": "The crown has fallen from our head; woe to us, for we have sinned!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:17",
      "text": "For this our heart has become sick, for these things our eyes have grown dim,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:18",
      "text": "for Mount Zion which lies desolate; jackals prowl over it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:19",
      "text": "But thou, O Lord, dost reign for ever; thy throne endures to all generations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:20",
      "text": "Why dost thou forget us for ever, why dost thou so long forsake us?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:21",
      "text": "Restore us to thyself, O Lord, that we may be restored! Renew our days as of old!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:lamentations.5.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:22",
      "text": "Or hast thou utterly rejected us? Art thou exceedingly angry with us?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
